class_description:
You typically use instances of NSUnitPressure to represent specific quantities of pressure using the NSMeasurement class.
Pressure is the normal force over a surface. The SI unit for pressure is the pascal (Pa), which is derived as one newton of force over one square meter (1Pa = 1N / 1m2).
The NSUnitPressure class defines its base unit as newtonsPerMeterSquared, and provides the following units, which are initialized using UnitConverterLinear converters with the specified coefficients:
